# API service types colocation

When adding or editing **service** modules under `apps/api`, keep **interfaces**, **type aliases**, and **shared request/response or row shapes** out of `*.service.ts`. Put them in the **adjacent** file `<same-base-name>.types.ts` in the same directory, and import from there.

## Naming

| Service file | Types file |
|--------------|------------|
| `foo.service.ts` | `foo.types.ts` |

## Rules

- **Export** types that the service or its callers need from `*.types.ts`.
- **`*.service.ts`** holds implementation (classes, functions, queries). Only imports types from `./<name>.types` (and shared libs), not inline `interface` / `type` definitions for API shapes.
- **Shared types** used only by this service module stay in that `*.types.ts`. If multiple services need the same shape, prefer a shared types module only when the codebase already uses that pattern.

## Example

```ts
// chart-pull-request.types.ts — filters, SQL helper shapes, chart row types
export interface PullRequestFlowChartFilters { /* ... */ }
export interface PullRequestFiltersResult { /* ... */ }

// chart-pull-request.service.ts
import {
  PullRequestFlowChartFilters,
  PullRequestFiltersResult,
} from "./chart-pull-request.types";
```

```ts
// ❌ Avoid — interfaces / row DTOs defined in *.service.ts
// ✅ Prefer — my-feature.types.ts beside my-feature.service.ts
```
